  "texts": [
    "By examining heterogenous effects across different project activity levels, and by leveraging documented model upgrades, we can determine whether the gap between iterative and capability innovation narrows, widens, or remains stable as LLM context understanding improves.",
    "We study these questions by analyzing languages in pairs: first pair comparing Python (supported) and R (unsupported), and second comparing Rust (supported) and Haskell (unsupported).",
    "Python/R are dataoriented languages with similar ecosystems focused on analytics, machine learning, and statistical computing.",
    "Rust and Haskell are performance-oriented compiled languages emphasizing systems programming and functional paradigms.",
    "This pairing approach allows us to test robustness across different programming domains while maintaining comparability of treated and control packages."
  ],
